{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan an Nasai","section":{"1":{"eng-name":"The Book of Purification","ara-name":"كتاب الطهارة"}},"section_detail":{"1":{"hadithnumber_first":1,"hadithnumber_last":324,"arabicnumber_first":1,"arabicnumber_last":324}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":214,"arabicnumber":214,"text":"It was narrated from Jabir bin 'Abdullah, in the Hadith of Asma' bint 'Umair, when she gave birth in Dhul-Hulaifah, that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said to Abu Bakr:\"Tell her to perform Ghusl and enter Ihram","grades":[{"name":"Abu Ghuddah","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"}],"reference":{"book":1,"hadith":215},"chapter":{"id":137,"ara-name":"باب الاِغْتِسَالِ مِنَ النِّفَاسِ","eng-name":"Performing Ghusl From Nifas (Postnatal Bleeding)","isFirstHadith":true}}]}